Previously, the InternApplicationCard display the fields in the wrong order. Let's change it to Company, Role, Cycle, Status, Deadline, Notes.

In our discussion, status field is supposed to be optional. I have made
the changes in this commit.

In addition, I have also made the comparison on whether an Intern
Application already exists if all of following fields are the same:
* Company Name
* Role
* Cycle

The reason is because, a user may apply for the same company with
different role or at a different cycle.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Cycle to allow for hyphens
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, Cycle only accepts alphanumeric characters.

We want Cycle to accept hyphens as valid input
e.g. "Off-cycle 2025"

Let's update the regex and test cases for Cycle.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add find command to user guide
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command was previously removed from the original AB3
user guide.

The find command will be used in the new InternTracker application.

Let's,
add the find command back to the user guide.

AB3 Behaviour for search is based on keywords using
the CompanyContainsKeywordPredicate class.
Search "Jane" -> "Jane street"
Search "Google Meta" will match "Google" and "Meta"

Let's update the find command to be more intuitive for searching company names.
Specifically, let's
Create a new class called CompanyPartialMatchPredicate which
has the following behaviour
Search "jan" -> "Jane Street"
Search "JAN" -> "Jane Street"
Search "jst" -> "Jane Street"
Search "Google Meta" doesnâ€™t match anything

Currently, we cannot sort by internship deadline.

Let's add sorting by internship deadline to the existing
sort logic.

Implementing the comparable interface for each
field in the Model will simplify the sorting process.
Add some assertions for methods associated with undo and view.

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, deadlines such as 31 Feb 2023 are accepted.

Let's update the logic to be more strict with parsing.
Note that yyyy is changed to uuuu as "uuuu" signifies "year" and
does not rely on the era.

See this link for reference:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/60779696/localdate-datetimeformatter-problems
